          <section aria-labelledby="theory" class="prose">
            <h2 id="theory">Formulas and explanation</h2>
            <p><strong>1 knot</strong> is defined as <strong>1 nautical mile per hour</strong>. A nautical mile is standardized as <strong>1.852 km</strong> or about <strong>1.15078 miles</strong>. From this we get:</p>
            <div class="formula-box">
              <code>mph = knots × 1.15078</code><br>
              <code>km/h = knots × 1.852</code>
            </div>
            <p>If you only need a quick mental estimate, you can use:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>mph ≈ knots × 1.15</li>
              <li>km/h ≈ knots × 1.85</li>
            </ul>

