          <section aria-labelledby="faq" class="prose mt-10">
            <h2 id="faq">FAQ</h2>
            <h3>Why do ships and planes use knots?</h3>
            <p>Because nautical miles tie directly to latitude/longitude (1 NM = 1 minute of arc of latitude). This makes navigation and charting much simpler.</p>

            <h3>Is the factor 1.852 exact?</h3>
            <p>Yes — the international nautical mile is exactly 1.852 kilometers.</p>

            <h3>What about wind speed reports?</h3>
            <p>Meteorological and marine weather reports often quote wind in knots to match nautical practice. This converter gives you mph and km/h instantly.</p>
